2. meat;
3. milk and milk products;
4. eggs and poultrymeat;
5. diverse animal products (auction markets);
6. cereals and rice;
7. oil producing plants (olive oil);
8. wine and alcohol;
9. fruit and vegetables;
10. flowers and plants;
11. potatoes;
(b) an indicative financing plan specifying, at constant 1991 prices, the total cost of the priorities adopted for joint action by the Community and the Member State concerned, ECU 316 388 599 for the whole period, and the financial arrangements envisaged for budgetary assistance from the Community, broken down as follows:
(ecus)
1. forestry products 12 283 255 2. meat 14 166 358 3. milk and milk products 25 961 874 4. eggs and poultrymeat 2 745 617 5. diverse animal products (auction markets) 2 483 256 6. cereals and rice 8 174 694 7. oil producing plants (olive oil) 5 308 994 8. wine and alcohol 26 748 714 9. fruit and vegetables 23 194 638 10. flowers and plants 1 625 215 11. potatoes 2 031 518 Total 124 724 103
